<br>
I picture this and wonder what the Lord of the Rings would look like if enacted with EQ game mechanics, and all I can do is laugh. Tolkien could have done so much better with an EQ based world. Course - the Lord of the Rings would be a comedy. I hope EQ2 deals with this stuff, since after 3 years - EQ1 hasn't. <br>
<br>
The fellowship meets a party of orcs: <br>
Legolas fires his bow at an_Orc_01, but can't see his target because the orc is standing on a step 2 inches down. Gandalf has the same problem with his projectile fireball. Luckily - the Orc hasn't noticed them yet. <br>
<br>
Gandalf casts his Ice Comet spell at an_Orc_01, but it is resisted. The entire Orc party heads straight for Gandalf. Gandalf starts running around the Fellowship in big circles, hair and robes flying behind him. Legolas lines up another shot while Aragorn, Boromir, the Hobbits, and Gimli chase the Orcs down from behind. The orcs ignore the rest of the fellowship and continue to chase Gandalf. <br>
<br>
The fellowship slays the party of orcs and sees an_Orc_05 was 2 steps too far away to notice his friends attack. Merry sneaks up behind him, carefully lines up a stab to the orc's back, and misses. The Orc notices the dagger, turns around and begins pounding on Merry. Boromir charges to the rescue, calls the Orc a sissy and the orc turns his back on Merry to attack Boromir. Merry lines up a backstab while the orc is engaged with Boromir and wham - lots of damage. The orc turns back around and starts whacking on Merry again. Boromir calls the orc a sissy again, but the orc continues to smack Merry. Merry somehow manages to hide WHILE the orc is beating on him, so the orc turns back around and starts whacking on Boromir. Aragorn calls on his ranger abilities to deliver healing to the battered Merry. Aragorn takes a seat to regain some of the magic power he expended to heal Merry. The orc looks up, notices that Aragorn has sat down, and becomes enraged. He stops beating on Boromir and runs over to Aragorn and starts pounding on him. Aragorn stands up to defend himself, and the orc suddenly remembers that he left Boromir alone. The orc runs back and starts beating on Boromir again. Legolas tries a few shots but his arrows magically disappear since they can't get through the now standing Aragorn. The orc realizes he's almost dead and decides to make a break for it - at a turtles pace. He actually stops fighting and starts inching away. His health and lifesblood continue to leak out a a pretty fast pace but the orc still thinks he can get away, even though Merry and Boromir are easily keeping up with him. Aragorn snares the orc as it's 'running' so that it can't move. The orc still thinks it can get away so it doesn't fight back. Gandalf puts the orc out of his misery with a well placed nuke, but is upset when he doesn't get a skill increase.<br>
<br>
Thought you guys would like this I was laughing so hard i had tears in my eyes. lol I love Lord of the rings.. See ya in Norrath<br>
